<capabilities>
The early version of the Partisan was equipped with four medium autocannons mounted on a quad turret, firing proximity-fused rounds for greater accuracy against airborne targets. These weapons were key to its effectiveness against aircraft, aided by the Anti Air Flak Systems-1 tracking and targeting equipment. The later version of the Partisan incorporated integral C3 computers, a significant upgrade that allowed the tank to link with an entire company, thereby improving its targeting capabilities. This version's armament included a pair of Imperator Code Red LB 10-X autocannons and Smoothie light autocannons, chosen for their compatibility with advanced munitions like precision-guided and armor-piercing rounds.
</capabilities>

<overview>
